    <artifactId>service-limit</artifactId>
    <packaging>jar</packaging>
    <name>service-limit</name>
    <description>A microservice that stores the configurations per player and domain on matters such as betting and deposit limits, self exclusions etc. The service proxies most requests to other storage systems where limits are checked, but services as a base for the business logic of such requests. A bet subsystem will check with service-limit if betting limits are reach, while service-limit will check its configurations on the limits for the player, and in turn make a call to service-accounting to get up to date statistics for the users betting history to ascertain whether the bet should be allowed.</description>
    
